# Loan Management App - User Requirements Document

## 1. Executive Summary

### 1.1 Project Overview
The Loan Management App is a comprehensive mobile application designed to streamline the entire loan lifecycle, from application to closure. The app serves multiple user types including customers, loan officers, and administrators, providing a secure, efficient, and user-friendly platform for loan management.

### 1.2 Business Objectives
- **Increase Loan Application Efficiency**: Reduce application processing time by 50%
- **Improve Customer Experience**: Provide 24/7 self-service capabilities
- **Enhance Risk Management**: Implement automated credit scoring and fraud detection
- **Reduce Operational Costs**: Automate manual processes and reduce paperwork
- **Ensure Compliance**: Meet all regulatory requirements for financial services

### 1.3 Success Metrics
- Loan application completion rate: > 80%
- Customer satisfaction score: > 4.5/5
- Average loan processing time: < 48 hours
- Payment on-time rate: > 95%
- Document verification success rate: > 90%

## 2. User Personas

### 2.1 Primary Users

#### 2.1.1 Customer (Borrower)
**Profile**: Individual seeking personal or business loans
**Goals**:
- Apply for loans easily and quickly
- Track application status in real-time
- Make payments conveniently
- Access loan information and history
- Upload required documents securely

**Pain Points**:
- Complex application processes
- Lack of transparency in loan status
- Difficulty in making payments
- Poor communication from lenders

#### 2.1.2 Loan Officer
**Profile**: Bank employee responsible for loan processing
**Goals**:
- Review and approve loan applications efficiently
- Access comprehensive customer information
- Track loan portfolio performance
- Communicate with customers effectively
- Ensure compliance with regulations

**Pain Points**:
- Manual data entry and processing
- Difficulty accessing customer information
- Lack of automated decision support
- Poor integration between systems

#### 2.1.3 Administrator
**Profile**: System administrator managing the platform
**Goals**:
- Monitor system performance and security
- Manage user accounts and permissions
- Generate reports and analytics
- Configure system settings
- Ensure data integrity and compliance

**Pain Points**:
- Complex system administration
- Limited reporting capabilities
- Security vulnerabilities
- Poor audit trail

### 2.2 Secondary Users

#### 2.2.1 Credit Bureau
- Provide credit reports and scores
- Receive payment history updates
- Access fraud detection data

#### 2.2.2 Payment Gateway
- Process loan payments
- Handle multiple payment methods
- Provide transaction confirmations

## 3. Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Authentication & User Management

#### 3.1.1 User Registration
**REQ-AUTH-001**: Customer Registration
- Users can register using email/phone and password
- Social login integration (Google, Apple, Facebook)
- Email/phone verification required (OTP)
- KYC (Know Your Customer) verification process (NO HAVE)
- Profile completion with personal information

**REQ-AUTH-002**: Multi-Factor Authentication
- SMS/email OTP verification
- Biometric authentication (fingerprint, face ID)
- Two-factor authentication for sensitive operations
- Session management and timeout

**REQ-AUTH-003**: Role-Based Access Control
- Customer role with limited access
- Loan Officer role with application management
- Administrator role with full system access
- Permission-based feature access

#### 3.1.2 Profile Management
**REQ-PROF-001**: Customer Profile
- Personal information (name, address, contact details)
- Employment and income information
- Bank account details
- Emergency contacts
- Profile picture and document uploads

**REQ-PROF-002**: Profile Updates
- Real-time profile updates
- Document verification status
- Credit score display
- Loan history and payment records

### 3.2 Loan Application Management

#### 3.2.1 Loan Application Process
**REQ-LOAN-001**: Application Creation
- Multiple loan types (personal, business, mortgage, auto)
- Loan amount and term selection
- Purpose of loan specification
- Interest rate calculation and display
- Monthly payment estimation

**REQ-LOAN-002**: Document Upload
- Required document checklist
- Multiple file format support (PDF, JPG, PNG)
- Document preview and validation
- Upload progress tracking
- Document verification status

**REQ-LOAN-003**: Application Status Tracking
- Real-time application status updates
- Status change notifications
- Timeline view of application progress
- Estimated processing time
- Communication history with loan officer

#### 3.2.2 Credit Assessment
**REQ-CREDIT-001**: Credit Score Integration
- Automatic credit score retrieval
- Credit report display
- Credit history analysis
- Risk assessment and scoring
- Credit improvement recommendations

**REQ-CREDIT-002**: Income Verification
- Employment verification
- Income documentation upload
- Bank statement analysis
- Debt-to-income ratio calculation
- Financial capacity assessment

### 3.3 Loan Management

#### 3.3.1 Loan Approval Process
**REQ-APPROVAL-001**: Application Review
- Loan officer dashboard for applications
- Application details and document review
- Credit score and risk assessment
- Approval/rejection decision interface
- Comments and feedback system

**REQ-APPROVAL-002**: Loan Disbursement
- Loan agreement generation
- Digital signature collection
- Fund transfer initiation
- Disbursement confirmation
- Welcome kit and instructions

#### 3.3.2 Loan Monitoring
**REQ-MONITOR-001**: Loan Dashboard
- Active loan summary
- Payment schedule and history
- Outstanding balance and interest
- Next payment due date
- Loan performance metrics

**REQ-MONITOR-002**: Payment Tracking
- Payment history with details
- Payment method management
- Late payment tracking
- Payment reminders and notifications
- Payment receipt generation

### 3.4 Payment Management

#### 3.4.1 Payment Processing
**REQ-PAYMENT-001**: Payment Methods
- Bank transfer integration
- Credit/debit card payments
- Digital wallet support (PayPal, Apple Pay)
- Cash deposit at branches
- Automatic recurring payments

**REQ-PAYMENT-002**: Payment Scheduling
- One-time payment scheduling
- Recurring payment setup
- Payment date modification
- Payment amount adjustment
- Payment cancellation

#### 3.4.2 Payment History
**REQ-HISTORY-001**: Transaction Records
- Complete payment history
- Transaction details and receipts
- Payment method used
- Status and confirmation
- Export functionality

### 3.5 Communication & Notifications

#### 3.5.1 Push Notifications
**REQ-NOTIFY-001**: System Notifications
- Application status updates
- Payment reminders and confirmations
- Document verification status
- Loan approval/rejection notifications
- System maintenance alerts

**REQ-NOTIFY-002**: Communication Center
- In-app messaging system
- Chat with loan officers
- Message history and search
- File sharing in conversations
- Read receipts and status

### 3.6 Reporting & Analytics

#### 3.6.1 Customer Reports
**REQ-REPORT-001**: Personal Reports
- Loan summary reports
- Payment history reports
- Credit score reports
- Tax documents (1098-E)
- Annual statements

#### 3.6.2 Administrative Reports
**REQ-REPORT-002**: Business Intelligence
- Loan portfolio analytics
- Application conversion rates
- Payment performance metrics
- Customer satisfaction scores
- Risk assessment reports

## 4. Non-Functional Requirements

### 4.1 Performance Requirements

#### 4.1.1 Response Time
**REQ-PERF-001**: Application Performance
- App launch time: < 3 seconds
- Page load time: < 2 seconds
- API response time: < 1 second
- Image upload time: < 30 seconds for 10MB
- Payment processing: < 10 seconds

#### 4.1.2 Scalability
**REQ-SCALE-001**: System Capacity
- Support 10,000+ concurrent users
- Handle 1,000+ loan applications per day
- Process 5,000+ payments per hour
- Store 1TB+ of documents
- 99.9% uptime requirement

### 4.2 Security Requirements

#### 4.2.1 Data Protection
**REQ-SEC-001**: Data Security
- End-to-end encryption for all data
- Secure storage of sensitive information
- Regular security audits and penetration testing
- Compliance with PCI DSS standards
- GDPR compliance for data handling

#### 4.2.2 Authentication Security
**REQ-SEC-002**: Access Control
- Strong password requirements
- Account lockout after failed attempts
- Session timeout and automatic logout
- Audit trail for all user actions
- Secure API authentication

### 4.3 Usability Requirements

#### 4.3.1 User Interface
**REQ-UI-001**: Design Standards
- Material Design 3.0 compliance
- Accessibility standards (WCAG 2.1)
- Multi-language support (English, Spanish, Vietnamese)
- Dark mode support
- Responsive design for all screen sizes

#### 4.3.2 User Experience
**REQ-UX-001**: Ease of Use
- Intuitive navigation and workflow
- Clear error messages and guidance
- Offline functionality for critical features
- Progressive web app capabilities
- Voice input support for accessibility

### 4.4 Reliability Requirements

#### 4.4.1 System Reliability
**REQ-REL-001**: Availability
- 99.9% system uptime
- Automatic failover and recovery
- Data backup and disaster recovery
- Monitoring and alerting systems
- Performance degradation handling

#### 4.4.2 Data Integrity
**REQ-INT-001**: Data Accuracy
- Real-time data synchronization
- Conflict resolution mechanisms
- Data validation and verification
- Audit logging for all changes
- Data consistency across platforms

## 5. Technical Requirements

### 5.1 Platform Requirements

#### 5.1.1 Mobile Platforms
**REQ-PLAT-001**: Device Support
- iOS 13.0 and above
- Android 8.0 (API level 26) and above
- Tablet support (iPad, Android tablets)
- Progressive Web App (PWA) support
- Cross-platform consistency

#### 5.1.2 Backend Integration
**REQ-BACKEND-001**: API Integration
- RESTful API architecture
- GraphQL support for complex queries
- Real-time WebSocket connections
- API versioning and backward compatibility
- Rate limiting and throttling

### 5.2 Integration Requirements

#### 5.2.1 Third-Party Services
**REQ-INTEG-001**: External Integrations
- Credit bureau APIs (Experian, Equifax, TransUnion)
- Payment gateway integration (Stripe, PayPal)
- Banking APIs for account verification
- Document verification services
- SMS/email service providers

#### 5.2.2 Data Synchronization
**REQ-SYNC-001**: Data Management
- Real-time data synchronization
- Offline data caching
- Conflict resolution strategies
- Data migration capabilities
- Backup and restore functionality

## 6. Compliance Requirements

### 6.1 Regulatory Compliance

#### 6.1.1 Financial Regulations
**REQ-COMP-001**: Financial Compliance
- PCI DSS compliance for payment processing
- SOX compliance for financial reporting
- Anti-money laundering (AML) requirements
- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations
- Local banking regulations

#### 6.1.2 Data Privacy
**REQ-PRIV-001**: Privacy Compliance
- GDPR compliance for EU users
- CCPA compliance for California users
- Data retention and deletion policies
- User consent management
- Privacy policy and terms of service

### 6.2 Audit Requirements

#### 6.2.1 Audit Trail
**REQ-AUDIT-001**: Audit Logging
- Complete audit trail for all transactions
- User action logging
- System access logging
- Data change tracking
- Audit report generation

## 7. User Stories

### 7.1 Customer User Stories

#### 7.1.1 Loan Application
**As a customer, I want to:**
- Apply for a loan online without visiting a branch
- Upload required documents easily
- Track my application status in real-time
- Receive notifications about my application
- Calculate loan payments before applying

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Application form is intuitive and easy to complete
- Document upload supports multiple formats
- Status updates are real-time and accurate
- Notifications are timely and informative
- Loan calculator provides accurate estimates

#### 7.1.2 Payment Management
**As a customer, I want to:**
- Make payments using multiple methods
- Schedule automatic payments
- View my payment history
- Receive payment reminders
- Download payment receipts

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Payment process is secure and fast
- Multiple payment methods are available
- Payment history is complete and searchable
- Reminders are sent at appropriate times
- Receipts are generated automatically

### 7.2 Loan Officer User Stories

#### 7.2.1 Application Review
**As a loan officer, I want to:**
- Review loan applications efficiently
- Access customer information quickly
- Make approval/rejection decisions
- Communicate with customers
- Track application processing time

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Application dashboard is comprehensive
- Customer information is easily accessible
- Decision interface is user-friendly
- Communication tools are integrated
- Processing metrics are accurate

### 7.3 Administrator User Stories

#### 7.3.1 System Management
**As an administrator, I want to:**
- Monitor system performance
- Manage user accounts and permissions
- Generate reports and analytics
- Configure system settings
- Ensure data security

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Monitoring dashboard is comprehensive
- User management is efficient
- Reports are accurate and timely
- Configuration is flexible
- Security measures are effective

## 8. Acceptance Criteria

### 8.1 Functional Acceptance Criteria

#### 8.1.1 Core Functionality
- [ ] Users can register and authenticate successfully
- [ ] Loan applications can be submitted and processed
- [ ] Payments can be made and tracked
- [ ] Documents can be uploaded and verified
- [ ] Notifications are sent appropriately

#### 8.1.2 User Experience
- [ ] App is intuitive and easy to navigate
- [ ] All features work on supported devices
- [ ] Performance meets specified requirements
- [ ] Error handling is user-friendly
- [ ] Accessibility requirements are met

### 8.2 Non-Functional Acceptance Criteria

#### 8.2.1 Performance
- [ ] Response times meet specified requirements
- [ ] System can handle expected load
- [ ] Offline functionality works correctly
- [ ] Data synchronization is reliable
- [ ] App performance is consistent

#### 8.2.2 Security
- [ ] All security requirements are implemented
- [ ] Data is encrypted appropriately
- [ ] Authentication is secure
- [ ] Audit logging is complete
- [ ] Compliance requirements are met

## 9. Constraints and Assumptions

### 9.1 Technical Constraints
- Must support existing banking infrastructure
- Limited to mobile platforms initially
- Must integrate with legacy systems
- Budget constraints for third-party services
- Timeline constraints for regulatory compliance

### 9.2 Business Constraints
- Must comply with financial regulations
- Limited to specific geographic regions initially
- Must support existing customer base
- Budget limitations for development
- Resource constraints for testing

### 9.3 Assumptions
- Users have basic smartphone literacy
- Internet connectivity is generally available
- Users are willing to provide personal information
- Regulatory environment remains stable
- Third-party services are reliable

## 10. Risk Assessment

### 10.1 Technical Risks
- **Data Security Breaches**: Implement comprehensive security measures
- **System Performance Issues**: Conduct thorough performance testing
- **Integration Failures**: Plan for fallback mechanisms
- **Scalability Challenges**: Design for future growth

### 10.2 Business Risks
- **Regulatory Changes**: Monitor regulatory environment
- **User Adoption**: Conduct user research and testing
- **Competition**: Differentiate through superior user experience
- **Economic Factors**: Plan for economic downturns

### 10.3 Mitigation Strategies
- Regular security audits and updates
- Comprehensive testing and quality assurance
- User feedback and iterative development
- Compliance monitoring and updates
- Performance monitoring and optimization

This user requirements document provides a comprehensive foundation for developing a successful loan management application that meets the needs of all stakeholders while ensuring compliance, security, and user satisfaction.
